{"summary":"All three amendments are technically sound. The first removes dead validation branches; the second and third identify real lineage/snapshot correctness bugs that can break idempotent repair or hide still-running work.","votes":[{"amendment_id":"fr-17-bcf4f863","decision":"accept","rationale":"`normalized.starts_with('.')` already rejects both `\".\"` and `\"..\"`, so the later equality checks are unreachable. Removing them preserves behavior and makes the identifier validation rule clearer and less misleading."},{"amendment_id":"fr-17-d6be598b","decision":"accept","rationale":"`record_bead_completion` discards `started_at`, and the runless update path in `FsTaskRunLineageStore::update_task_run` can only disambiguate by `(bead_id, project_id)` plus narrow replay heuristics. Once multiple runless attempts reuse the same project, terminal replay becomes ambiguous, so a partial completion write can no longer be repaired. That is a real correctness hole in the advertised retry/idempotency behavior."},{"amendment_id":"fr-17-c776961e","decision":"accept","rationale":"Start logic only blocks a different active bead, not another active attempt for the same bead. Snapshot reconciliation then collapses to the newest attempt per bead, which can hide an older still-running attempt and mark the milestone ready with `in_progress_beads = 0` while lineage still contains active work. That is an inconsistent state; the older running attempt must be rejected or explicitly superseded."}]}